name: Cascan
overview: Hailing from planet Cascareau in the Andromeda Galaxy, these aliens are very similar to Orishans, being armored humanoids able to manipulate water.

name: Cathar
overview: Cat-like humanoid

name: Celestialsapien
overview: Horned humanoids with a body similar to that of a starry night sky from the Forge of Creation, they can warp space, time and reality. However, they are limited by their psyche: their minds are divided into separate personalities that need to agree in order to do even simple tasks, causing them to remain motionless for long periods of time.

name: Centauri
overview: Humanoid

name: Centrans
overview: Feline humanoids

name: Cerebrocrustacean
overview: Crab-like aliens from Encephalonus IV with massive heads due to super-sized brains. They are extremely intelligent (their IQ is at one nonillion), though not as smart as Galvans, and can use their enhanced intelligence to perfectly calculate the trajectory of objects, operate complicated machinery, and come up with strategies for combat on the fly, and also generate and manipulate electricity into electric blasts and force fields.

overview: an alien empire; note: many of the "Combine" seen in the game are actually humans that have been assimilated or collaborate as brutal police troopers.

overview: The Control Brains assign the Irken race with roles and are the unspoken leaders of the Irken Empire.

overview: Humanoid

overview: Humanoid

name: Covenant
overview: Collective of alien species who are allied with each other, Composed of Grunts, Brutes, Elites, Hunters, Jackals, and Prophets. Religious Hierarchy with intent to destroy the Human Race.

name: Crystals
overview: Hi-tech aliens that has control over red crystals with unlimited powers, which are used to power up their weapons and equipment.

name: Crescendolls
overview: An alien band, inspired by the Daft Punk song of the same name.

name: Crites
overview: carnivorous hairballs

name: Cryons
overview: A crystalline humanoid race from planet Telos, they cannot survive temperatures above the freezing point, boiling and steaming in said temperatures.

name: Cybermen
overview: Marauding cybernetic life-forms. Originally an alien race driven to conversion by catastrophic climate change, more recently reimagined as assimilated humans.

name: Cybertronians
overview: Large robots from planet Cybertron able to change their shape at will into other mechanical constructs, most commonly varying types of vehicles like planes and trucks. Known more commonly as Transformers.

name: Cylons
overview: Sentient robots. Remnants of a civilization of reptilian aliens (also known as Cylons) in the original series, but created by humans in the remake series.  Both mechanical and biological flesh-and-blood versions co-exist, with the biological versions in charge.
